{"TopicId":181268,"ForumId":148,"TopicTitle":"Kerbal Space Program\u00A01.6.1\u00A0and\u00A0Making History\u00A01.6.1\u00A0is\u00A0live!","CreatedByName":"UomoCapra","CreatedById":167737,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-09T19:52:20Z","PageNum":5,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-17T05:42:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223522181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221547494912\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022131400\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starhawk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/14/2019 at 2:41 PM, Starhawk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s a pic during ascent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/O8rUbaL.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022O8rUbaL.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/O8rUbaL.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI basically (and inadvertently) copied this design for my own Eve lifter, though it was for one Kerbal, didn\u0027t have anything but the engines and tanks and the actual payload stage was totally different. Oh and I used fuel lines like old skool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought I was being creative with it but upon seeing this pic, I see I must have seen this first. It\u0027s a solid design that even I could fly. I was able to get into orbit from sea level in testing, and had fuel to spare launching from about 1km up in the actual mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhawk","CreatedById":131400,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-17T12:36:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223523733\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221547703746\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh and I used fuel lines like old skool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo skool like the old skool.\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EI\u0027ve found that I\u0027ve got used to building asparagus staged craft without fuel lines.\u00A0 The biggest downside for me was that I had to open and monitor the PAW for a tank in whichever stage was active to know when to stage it.\u00A0 Now, with the new \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E readouts, that is no longer an issue.\u00A0 The upsides are lower drag and part count.\u00A0 Plus, it seems so much less finicky to set up.\u00A0 YMMV.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EHappy landings!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jestersage","CreatedById":165777,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-21T22:32:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBTW, nice poster at the homepage.\u00A0 Really love the Mir clone. It does look familiar, however.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-21T23:53:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223526475\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548109935\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165777\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jestersage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Jestersage said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBTW, nice poster at the homepage.\u00A0 Really love the Mir clone. It does look familiar, however.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike Mir, perhaps? \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jestersage","CreatedById":165777,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-21T23:55:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223526517\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548114796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike Mir, perhaps? \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah. I know. It also resembles the layout of this guy:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Jestersage/RanGong-Outpost\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Jestersage/RanGong-Outpost\u003C/a\u003E. Granted, it\u0027s not a complete copy, look a bit too similar.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWho knows. a Mir clone is a Mir Clone. There can be only so many way to make each of the 6 modules...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-22T00:00:14Z\u0022 title=\u002201/22/2019 12:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 22, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Jestersage\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"F9800","CreatedById":193487,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-25T16:36:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003ENICE!\u00A0\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EdwardB3020","CreatedById":223607,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-26T12:54:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere\u0027s 1.7?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-26T13:14:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223529205\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548507255\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176465\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022EdwardB3020\uFEFF\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, EdwardB3020\uFEFF said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere\u0027s 1.7?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167737-uomocapra/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167737\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167737-uomocapra/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@UomoCapra\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0said in another thread that a KSP Loading (presumably with news about 1.7) is \u0027coming soon\u0027.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-26T13:56:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223529205\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548507255\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176465\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022EdwardB3020\uFEFF\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, EdwardB3020\uFEFF said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere\u0027s 1.7?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe plan is to release a new minor version every 3 months. So unless that has changed I expect 1.7 to drop some time in mid-March\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ruedii","CreatedById":57704,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-03T19:50:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have not personally had the issue, but some people have been complaining about performance issues with the new releases.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI strongly suspect that this has to do with the added rendering passes required for the reflective surfaces.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAdding an option to drastically reduce the quality of that pass, replace it with an algorithm that only reflects light emitters only or (for lowest quality) a simple specular algorithm.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nPreferably having all three options would be best.\u00A0 We all like shinies, but some of us like mods that hurt performance more when combined with them.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe other thing that might add issues is the Delta-V calculation system.\u00A0 All that can be done should be done to keep this routine garbage-free (Permanantly attaching the routine to the vessel object, using permanent data structures for any intermediary variables in the calculation and display process.\u00A0 Using fixed layout for display instead of dynamic.)\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAllowing the user to cap the refresh rate of all on-screen statistics and many other HUD objects should help.\u00A0\u00A0 Calculating them at a fixed rate instead of every frame would drastically reduce overhead.\u00A0 Generally the option should be give for 15 times a second 20 times a second, 30 times a second, 40 times a second, 60 times a second or every frame.\u00A0\u00A0 Since these are relatively static objects 20fps should be default on low performance computers, and 30 on high performance computers.\u00A0 Consoles should use 15 or 20 times a second.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\np.s. Sorry for the late reply, I just figured this was the right place to put it considering it is a release related issue.\u00A0 Based on feedback by other players I will make independent suggestions for these as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-02-03T19:51:14Z\u0022 title=\u002202/03/2019 07:51  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 3, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Ruedii\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Matuchkin","CreatedById":135127,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-14T03:22:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs much as we have progressed, we\u00A0 should all remember the version that would forever be in our hearts. 0.90, we shall never forget thee.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EdwardB3020","CreatedById":223607,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-16T19:57:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nresize the Gemini service module please?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-16T19:59:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223541878\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550347023\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176465\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022EdwardB3020\uFEFF\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, EdwardB3020\uFEFF said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nresize the Gemini service module please?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt has to be that shape to fit on a 1.875m MH Titan stack.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EdwardB3020","CreatedById":223607,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-16T20:05:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223541880\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550347158\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183830\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealKerbal3x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, RealKerbal3x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt has to be that shape to fit on a 1.875m MH Titan stack.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI guess scale down the pod slightly,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-16T20:28:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223541886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550347530\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176465\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022EdwardB3020\uFEFF\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, EdwardB3020\uFEFF said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI guess scale down the pod slightly,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that would probably only make it useful for Gemini recreations. The whole point of KSP is being modular and LEGO-like, so having just that pod at its own unique size would just limit possible designs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-17T22:23:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223540385\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550114569\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135127\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Matuchkin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E2\u200E/\u200E13\u200E/\u200E2019 at 10:22 PM, Matuchkin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs much as we have progressed, we\u00A0 should all remember the version that would forever be in our hearts. 0.19, we shall never forget thee.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFixed that for ya.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ruedii","CreatedById":57704,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-06T07:11:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223540385\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550114569\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135127\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Matuchkin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/13/2019 at 10:22 PM, Matuchkin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs much as we have progressed, we\u00A0 should all remember the version that would forever be in our hearts. 0.90, we shall never forget thee. \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1.0 and 0.9 were the biggest leaps forward.\u00A0 I liked 1.0 the most because of the improved aerodynamics.\u00A0 Not everyone liked that change, though.\u00A0 (For those of us who previously used \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E, it was simply using the same flight and design techniques.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}